 Brasil|Brasil de Pelotas]] as a [[Midfielder|defensive midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nIn the summer 2019, Ananias joined Latvian club [[FK Ventspils]]. However, he left the club two months later after playing only one cup game for the club. He returned to Brazil to play for futsal team N\u00e1utico Fut7.<ref>[https://globoesporte.globo.com/pe/futebol/times/nautico/noticia/de-volta-da-europa-joao-ananias-reforca-time-fut7-do-nautico-para-manter-forma.ghtml De volta da Europa, Jo\u00e3o Ananias refor\u00e7a time fut7 do N\u00e1utico para manter forma], globoesporte.globo.com, 28 August 2019</ref> On 4 November it was announced, that he would join [[R\u00edver Atl\u00e9tico Clube]] from the 2020 season.<ref>[https://www.gp1.com.br/noticias/joao-ananias-e-o-mais-novo-reforco-do-river-para-temporada-2020-465690.html Jo\u00e3o Ananias \u00e9 o mais novo refor\u00e7o do River para temporada 2020], gpl.com.br, 4 November 2019</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|joao-ananias-jordao-junior/185661}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Brazil|Association football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ananias, Joao}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Clube N\u00e1utico Capibaribe players]]\n[[Category:W Connection F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Santa Cruz Futebol Clube players]]\n[[Category:Cuiab\u00e1 Esporte Clube players]]\n[[Category:Salgueiro Atl\u00e9tico Clube players]]\n[[Category:Joinville Esporte Clube players]]\n[[Category:FK Ventspils players]]\n[[Category:River Atl\u00e9tico Clube players]]\n[[Category:Gr\u00eamio Esportivo Brasil players]]\n[[Category:Latvian Higher League players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie B players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Trinidad and Tobago]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Trinidad and Tobago]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Latvia]]\n\n{{Brazil-footy-midfielder-1990s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "know > known", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jo%C3%A3o_Ananias"}
{"title_page": "Persipal Palu", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club \n|  clubname  = Persipal Palu\n|  image     = \n|  fullname  = Persatuan Sepak Bola Indonesia Palu\n|  nickname  = ''The [[Cuscus]]'' {{br}} ''Tadulako Army''\n|  founded   = 1977\n|  ground    = [[Gawalise Stadium]] <br />[[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]]\n|  capacity  = 30,000 \n|  owner     = PT. Palu Raya Sportindo\n|  chairman  = Rusdi Mastura\n|  manager   = Ir. Bartholomeus Tandilaga, CES\n|  CEO       = \n|  coach     = Erwin Soemampow\n|  league    = [[Liga 3 (Indonesia)]]\n|  season    = [[2016 Liga Nusantara|2016]]\n|  position  = National Round\n}}\n\n'''Persipal''' or '''Persipal Palu''' or '''Persatuan Sepak Bola Indonesia Palu''' ([[English language|en]]: ''[[Football Association of Indonesia]] Palu'') is an  [[Indonesia]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]]. Club played in [[Liga Nusantara]]. \n\nPersipal stadium named [[Gawalise Stadium]]. Its location was in downtown [[Duyu Village]], [[Districts of West Palu]], [[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]].\n\n==Honours==\n*[[Liga Indonesia Second Division]] '''Champions:''' 1996/97\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101126195807/http://liga-indonesia.co.id/bli/index.php?go=news.clubdetail&type=profile&klub=85 Persipal Palu] at Liga-Indonesia.co.id\n\n{{Football in Indonesia}}\n{{Indonesian Football League}}\n{{2010-11 in Indonesian football}}\n{{Liga Indonesia seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:1977 establishments in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1977]]\n[[Category:Palu]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-footyclub-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club \n|  clubname  = Persipal Palu\n|  image     = \n|  fullname  = Persatuan Sepak Bola Indonesia Palu\n|  nickname  = ''The [[Cuscus]]'' {{br}} ''Tadulako Army''\n|  founded   = 1977\n|  ground    = [[Gawalise Stadium]] <br />[[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]]\n|  capacity  = 30,000 \n|  owner     = PT. Palu Raya Sportindo\n|  chairman  = Rusdi Mastura\n|  manager   = Ir. Bartholomeus Tandilaga, CES\n|  CEO       = \n|  coach     = Erwin Soemampow\n|  league    = [[Liga 3 (Indonesia)]]\n|  season    = [[2016 Liga Nusantara|2016]]\n|  position  = National Round\n}}\n\n'''Persipal''' or '''Persipal Palu''' or '''Persatuan Sepak Bola Indonesia Palu''' ([[English language|en]]: ''[[Football Association of Indonesia]] Palu'') is an  [[Indonesia]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]]. Club played in [[Liga Nusantara]]. \n\nPersipal stadium named [[Gawalise Stadium]]. Its location was in downtown [[Duyu Village]], [[Districts of West Palu]], [[Palu]], [[Central Sulawesi]].\n\n==Honours==\n*[[Liga Indonesia Second Division]] '''Champions:''' 1996/97\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101126195807/http://liga-indonesia.co.id/bli/index.php?go=news.clubdetail&type=profile&klub=85 Persipal Palu] at Liga-Indonesia.co.id\n\n{{Football in Indonesia}}\n{{Indonesian Football League}}\n{{2010-11 in Indonesian football}}\n{{Liga Indonesia seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:1977 establishments in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1977]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-footyclub-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:PaluusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persipal_Palu"}
